{
  "text": "In the coding-space, it was possible to use simple, linear thresholds to assign DINs to different subgroups, which supported our initial empirical grouping [CITATION_1] . This opens the door to easily sort DINs recorded in different contexts. For example, spike trains obtained from extracellular multi-electrode array recordings (e.g., see [CITATION_2] ) could thus be linked to intracellular recordings. The data-driven analysis and the coding-space presented here will therefore be useful for a deeper analysis of different mechanosensory DIN populations.",
